The body of former Education CS George Magoha on Friday arrived at Yala ahead of the burial on Saturday. Family, friends and residents gathered at the Yala Township Primary School where the plane carrying Magoha's body landed. The body arrived shortly after 2 pm. On Thursday, family and friends held a requiem mass on Thursday at the Consolata Shrine, Westlands. The funeral mass will be held at Odera Akang'o University College Campus in Yala. Magoha died on January 24, at the Nairobi Hospital surrounded by his family and loved ones following a cardiac arrest.